<DocsPageShell
  title="Continuity And Memory"
  description="Memory is only part of the story. The larger goal is continuity: helping the agent resume itself, its work, and its relationships without constant re-briefing."
  eyebrow="Operator Guide"
  canonical="https://ouroboros.bot/docs/continuity-and-memory"
  intro="This page stays conceptual on purpose. Exact implementation details around continuity should come from the current code, logs, or bundle state your agent is already inside."
  noteTitle="Recommended handoff"
  noteBody="For a deeper dive, point your agent at /skills/use-sliding-context.md and tell it to inspect the latest local source before answering."
>
  <section class="grid gap-5 md:grid-cols-2">
    <PromptCard
      prompt={`Explain how continuity works in this current Ouroboros install. Inspect the live source or bundle, then tell me how the agent keeps the thread across sessions and interruptions.`}
      footnote="Use this when you want the current implementation, not a static concept article."
    />
    <PromptCard
      prompt={`Inspect how friend notes, memory, and cross-session context work right now. Tell me where quick social notes should go and how they differ from broader memory.`}
      footnote="Use this when the question is about people, relationships, and lightweight notes."
    />
  </section>

  <section class="grid gap-5 lg:grid-cols-[0.95fr_1.05fr]">
